lls or whatever it was, but - then she would say, now it's time for to get washed. I would wash myself then my sister Lizzie would do it, then - my mother had to wash my brother right enough. He was younger. And - we would all get the pyjamas on and all a
n
d away to bed. Say our prayers before we're going away to our bed. That's the way we were trained, ay. Now - now the children course at you. That's what I can't get away with. Ay. I say, oh my - these days certainly have changed, the people laugh - here a
t me. I said, listen the children of nowadays are not getting brought up, they're getting dragged up. According to the life I had when I was young, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 don
\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600  know, I'm mesmerized I say, so I am. I saw a wee boy - I wasn't long here, two year up here. And he wouldn't be any more then three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 You weren't allowed to have any of your toys or books up to the table?
