No. No, oh no, nowhere near it. We had to clear the table and - one washed the dishes, the other dried them, and we - didn't make a mess, we d
idn't need to sweep the floor nor nothing, and then - she would say - there were none of this in our days nor wirelesses nor nothing, she used to say - if we wanted to do our homework - wy'd do - we done it after that - you could - maybe get the - my sist
er Lizzei was a great one for the dolls. She'd take the dolls out and - sit and play with them then - well a certain time at night we were ordered to wash ourself and go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 When could you leave the table, after everybody had finished?
