Well my father was - good too and all. But the sister in America - she - when my father would 
take us out for shoes - my mother didn't go on any - like - she used to - hold onto his coat - and he - I used to say, oh she's like a wee dog on a chain you know. She - he - he didn't make her a favourite, there were no favourites in the family. And I wo
uld be the other side of him. That was if my mother - didn't manage out, he took us you know. But - she seemed to - cling more to my father but he didna make any thing of it, we were all treated alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 If you were worried about anything would they listen to your worries?
