ause we never - got the - as I say - with the - we went to school, with - with our playmates we played in school with and that. But - none of them ever came up to our home. No. And then - when we were younger we went out there to that Rooken Glen - with t
he school, the teachers tools, years ago, we - we mingled about with the ones in our classes and that right enough. But not outside in the street. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
What kind of people do you think that your parents hoped you would all grow up to be How did the hope you'd turn out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well they just left it to us as we grew up you know what I mean. As I say - my mother died - at - when I was young at thirteen, but God spared the father to - fif - eighty-three when he died. We lose one good parent, but the other one was left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did they have any ambitions for you, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well - we didn't get much of a chance then with my mother dying young, probably she would have - put us maybe to something like my aunts probably, yes. You know, some skill. But then
 my father couldn't afford to - put us to anything with a small wages he had, to bring us up. That's what I said to you that cousin of mine, I said - listen Mamie - she was - was sitting and she said, listen Kathie, isn't it great to say - you come off ma
 
Rose people? I said, yes. But I said, wait a wee minute Mamie. I was brought up the same as you, with both - good parents. She said, yes. And went to school, but - we - we had what done us, I said, but - I said, my father had to work hard for us and bring
 
us up. She said, oh yes. But I said, do you know what lacked with us? My father, I said, couldn't afford it, nor my mother, I said - because - they hadn't the money - to put us to the high school to bring us out to be something, as we grew - up in years. 
But we - we didn't get that chance. And my parents, it was no fault of theirs. You know? So she said, yes, Kathy, but - you see were all trained up to - do right from wrong and - keep clean and - whatnot, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did they consider that was the important thing in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Aye. Clean. Oh we had to be clean. We - we - we - the - the dress maybe we went to school in the morning were - when we come in from school, there weren't a mark on it the way the kids are going about nowadays. But we could 
put another dress on. We had a wardrobe then right enough and - a sideboard and that. But the rest of the - furniture was - all wood as I tell you, we had to scrub snow white. Ay. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 And that you knew right from wrong?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Aye. Aye. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
And my parents never swore in their life. No obscene language. Now that's the no, they never fought my parents, never argued in their life. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 When grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Oh we had to walk into the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 You weren't allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Yes. Aye. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well we got checked, but we - I can't - mind a - anything like that ever of getting checked in my life by both parents. Now they never lifted a belt in our their life to us, none of them. No, - none of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 If you were punished what was the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well my - we would get a good scolding as I tell you. But I can't go back to that as I say, but - we never got - no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 thrashing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600  off of any of the parents. We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Who would scold you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
My father or - my father wasn't there, my mother. But we never gave - answered back to the parents the way they do now. Maybe - if - the parent - mother said - you'll
 do that. You'll do that, and if you say - oh no, I'm not doing it, she'll do it, we didn't - we didn't get the chance - we had to go right there and do it Aye, she was firm with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Can you remember any particular occasion when you were punished, doe
s any occasion stand out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 No. I can't - go back to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Can you remember how you felt about it at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
No. No. 'Cos I - we really didn't do nothing that we - really got checked for. We had to obey. We had so strict parents, that's wh
at I said. We - we - we - just - you were told to do that and you had to do it and - the other one next to me, she had to do her share too. If I scrubbed all the chairs and tables and stuff, she got all the shelf dishes to wash down and - and - jelly pans
 
to clean and whatnot, well, I would get it the following week to do, she changed it about. We had to do it. I always obey. We didn't say no. I can't - say that my parents ever lifted a belt to us. Never. We were never - we never got it. No, we never got t
he belt. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Would you say you got your idea of how to behave from you're your parents?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well we got it from both of - them, my aunts were very strict too. They were very strict the way they way they were brought up too you know. They were brough
t up - good parents too, and if - when we did go down to Partick there - to see them, they would say - granda was living then, my father's father - when I was about what - seven. Seven or eight and Lizzie was younger than me and we would go down and Aunt 
M
innie and Sarah would say - hello, and then we'd go ever and shake hands with granda, God rest him, and I would give him a poke of these - soft - tube sweets you know, and the oldest aunt - Sarah said to me one day, some day, what's that you're giving gra
n
da? So my - granda would answer back and say, I wouldn't speak you know, I just stuck my - poke bag. And - granda says, oh how you - a child not giving me nothing that - she shouldn't. You want to know what it is, it's a bag of lozenges. That's what he ca
l
led - I can mind that. And my aunt Minnie looked at the other one and said, dear, dear. So - they would say now take off your coats. We'd take the coats off, they made them of course, take the coats off and they would hang them on a hanger, oh they would 
h
ang on the hanger up at the door, and then they would say, have you had your dinner? And we said, oh yes, well - you haven't had your tea? We said, no, but we'll get it when we go home. And Aunt Minnie would say, you'll get it here. So - she was a baker t
o
o, she would get out a pan and make you - they have them in the shop, what they call wee muffins. We had that with bread and butter, and cheese and sometimes we got a banana and an orange or an apple. And then we - we - we got sweets, you know, but they n
e
ver gave us money. We didn't get money off them. The only time we get money off them - if they bought us something at Christmas, and then my Uncle John would bring them up - to the house to us and in Cameron Street, and they would - do; dress dolls for us
,
 the way a bride is with a bridal dress on. I had one that had black hair, and Lizzie had the one that was the fairest. We were never fought the piece out, not - none of the two of us, we never - had cause to - do anything but my aunts changed them you kn
ow, the - they knew we didn't fight because we never got the chance to fight with one another. No.
