e in Country Tyrone, and these - cousins of my father's, they weren't our aunts, cousins, their name was - wait now - Kathy - Haggins. They were dressmakers too, Kathy Haggin, and - Lena Haggin and - what her name? Lena Haggin and Kathy Haggin, and the ot
h
er - oh my - oh wait - and Josephine, they were three sisters well - they were three cousins of my fa - my father's side, but not our cousins but they were pretty - lovely people and they treated us - they treated us beautiful. They took us to the Grand F
air in - Country Tyrone, they took us to the market place, and they took us all over and - they really were wonderful people. And they made us dresses too, for - before we came over here to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, because they were dressmakers too. Well they never - I never saw any of them since then. Never. No, I didn't see them. I didn't see any of them since then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 But it was a good holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Oh it was beautiful, well I - I never got over to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} since then. No. Never got over. That's the only when I was el
even. Eleven years of age, 'cos my mother died then - when I was thirteen, we never got back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. We had a marvelous holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Can you tell me how you spend Saturdays when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Well - we got turn about of going to the silent p
ictures - when we were - round about maybe nine or ten. But only once on the Saturday. I - my turn would be the one Saturday and Liz - my sister Elizabeth, she'd be the following Saturday. Well I would have to stay in the house. I would go out with my mot
her for messages and - that and come in. But - we didn't do much work then with - only washed up dishes and that and - that and that was all you know. We didn't work so hard then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did you used to go to the silent pictures because of your fathe
r working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Well, we did in - mind we got in for a penny. A penny in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Was that cheap because your father worked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
No. That was the cost of - penny a - that we got in for. The matinees. But we had to go straight home to the house. Well see we were - we never was allowed to stay out, we just had to - go right home the way we were trained up. We had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 How about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well, we - the Sundays we went to Mass and then - down to my aunts in Partick. And then back home again to the house. You know. But we never got playing out in the streets, the way - they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did you wear different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Oh yes, different from through the week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 They were your best clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Were you allowed to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
No. Just straight home from - chapel and up to the house, to get what dinner and then down to Partick as I tell you and - see my aunts and then come home again and - get washed and go to bed and - there w
asn't - went - we both were at school then, my mother wasn't - ill then, and - we - just - the routine work. Just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 starting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 , go messages you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did your parents think it was wrong to play games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Well they - we didn't do it you know
, we never done it the way they do the now, out and playing - football and whatnot, we never done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 You think that was because your parents didn't like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 No, they were very very strict - very strict that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did they think it was wrong to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Well they didn't do - no - hard work in a Sunday, you know, just wash up the dishes and - things like that, nothing - like floors or anything like that, we - had it all done - through - before the Sabbath day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 And your parents used to go to Mass with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
No, my father went himself. Oh - oh, he went himself, aye. They went theirself we - went to the nine o'clock Mass. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 They used to go every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Oh yes, both of them. See they were in that Sacred Hearts Sodality
 at that time too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 What was this society that your mother and father were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 What was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Sacred Heart Sodality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 What did they do in that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Well they had to go to Communion - every - I think it was every first Su
nday of the month, and then my father apart from that done the nine Fridays of every month. He always done that. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 You and your brothers and sisters used to go separately to Mass?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 No, we all three of us all went together. Aye, my brother -
 sis - sister and me. Well, though - and the younger one didn't go - because she was too young. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did you go to a Sunday school?
