\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Were there any other social activities organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
No. Not 'til we grew up then and then both - both - both Lizzie and me were in the Children of Mary. The one in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}
 and me, we were in it for years, and - it was Sister Philomena - a nun that came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Dublin{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - was in charge of us. I was telling Sister Gregory.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 What did you do in the Children of Mary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Well - we went to outings then, and then - different
 places you know. We went - we went one time out to - Tollcross to see the bridge, time we went to - different places - you know. Out with the nun you know. To see them. Not on private buses, the cars in these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 So you'd occasionally go out with the Children of Mary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Yes. Well we were out at - as I say, Tollcross I think - I think that's where the blind people were, children they were. Not grown ups. And the nuns were there. Think it was either there - that was there or they were in the Nazar
eth House - out at - what district was that we were at? Dalbaith.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Did the church run any temperance club?
