Oh yes. The people that we lived amongst - sometimes I see - see them - well - not some more - the now when - I've - got up in years myself, but I think the people that we knew then - that knew my parents but I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 they\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600  all dead now but - 
at one time years ago, they - if I did see them, they would say, my, my - where do you stay now? I said, oh, I'm away up Maryhill now, staying in that and I would say - who are you? And then they would mention and then I could go back you see. I could go 
b
ack to maybe - Mrs Marshall, she stayed in - Nanson Street where we were when I was getting brought up there too, and - her daughters and - and then there were Mrs Hood - and - then there were Mrs - Sinclair, and these - all these people that were quite -
 ordinary working class people and - never made no - fuss nor no fighting, not - very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 sociable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600  people - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Can you ever remember seeing a policeman round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 Oh they never were not - nothing like that. The - the police in thos
e days didn't - go - need to go to the houses. They did - they didn't need to go to the houses for trouble.
\par 
