, Anne. She was making her first communion. And - my father said to me, come on, we're going round to the shop at - at Charing Cross, and they keep beautiful white material, you know, white. Well - I said all right da. We hadn't - we couldn't
 say - I'm not going, oh we couldn't answer back. All right, and I got my coat on, and my father got ready and away round to Charing Cross - for this material for Anne's dress for her first communion. Well - he bought about two and a half yards of it. Oh 
