Well I - I used to get then when I - grew up you know, get my pocket money for doing - the housework and messages and - looking after - I
 had the whole - end of the stick as I say and - and I used to get maybe - ten shillings off my father if he could afford it and if not I got five. But I used to have to - put it in the bank but - we - my father never touched that pocket money we - we got
. It was wee stools we had Margaret. You know them wee stools, and we put the money in it. Yes, and - you can go back to that, the wee -
