No. Well I could say - you mean - my father would come into a conversation about that. No. He never - inte
rfered with religion to - about anybody, although maybe - when we were in - in - Nanson Street there were very few - Catholics up that stair, the same - where we were in Abingdon Street, he never mingled with none of them. He just kept - to himself and ke
pt off to what he was. He never fought the piece out about religion in his life. I don't do it either. No.
