ith him, away you go but give me the child, this was me. My father said that for a laugh, you know. Give me the child, away you go with him. So that was that. Aye. That was that, but my father was very - witty that way. But she'd never have done it, see t
he man as only - she was only - saying that to him you know. He'd been in her life when she was younger over in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Ireland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 likely, and - then she told him she was married. So my - my dad said, well - if you want to go away with him, away you go, I'll take the 
child and - mother laughed. So that was how he told us about it, he used to tell us all that when we were younger Margaret, and he would sit us around, you see, and we were - quite interested in how he was brought up and all the rest of it, but you'll no 
get the parents doing that nowadays. You won't. You'll no get them doing it. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Can you remember any rough music ever being made? Have you ever heard of rough music?
