No, not in they days, no. They'd no wirelesses in they days nor nothing like that. But we had the piano but my father played it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Rough music was something slightly different, it was when people used to go and stand outside a house of somebody they didn't approved of or didn't like and they'd bang cans together or shout and
 make noises to show they disapproved of these people. Did they do that in Maryhill?
