Well I was at the hot plate you know, only - in the Beresford, that was my one job and one j
ob only. Well - I was six year in it as I told you and I - I was there and the baby - Mary nearly born in it, well - I left the Beresford - and I went into - the Codora, and I was in the Codor - no. No, no. Not the Codora. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, well - I went down 
there, I got all my own jobs, I never got - nothing, my registration offices dear that you pay money to go and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12853325\charrsid7227600 get}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600  the job. I hadna the money to go and - get the jobs so I - I went myself and interviewed all the hotels and went round 'til I got them, and t
hen I told them I had done six year in Beresford. Well - I goes into this {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. It's there yet, but it's different hands that's got it now, to when I was in it. Well here - I was away in the - big swivel doors and right down - and down to the kitch
en. So here you talk about that wee boy that - that Kathy's got. He - as I'm telling you - you know, the chef, well that child's the same, well - anyway, I goes away in, but he hadnae the long hair the chef you know, and he had the chef's clothes on. So I
 
said, are you the head chef? Aye, he says, I'm the head chef. And he could speak Scotch. The chink. Chinese. So here - and I knew he was a Chinese with the wee tight eyes and the yellow skin you know, and the white showed it up more, it - the white suit y
o
u see, and the big - hat and - well - he said, would you like a job? What do you do? Well I says, I - I've done six year in Beresford - I said, at the hot plate. He says, what? He says, you'll be able to start here. I says, what? Well I says I done six ye
a
r with - would you like to phone them up? Not at all he says. Well he says, that would be lovely here. He says, because - he says, they won't stand at the heat of the hot plate here. They're in one day and out the next. I said, oh no. If I like the job I 
s
ays I'll stay, except Sunday. I - I - was a thing my, I'll walk out. So I tell if you whoever's on under me that I'll get a better job maybe, so if it doesn't suit me so here, he; said, would you like to start here? And I said, all right chef. He said, we
l
l you'll go to the hot plate - breakfast and lunches. That's the one shift. And then - at night you've - high teas and dinner. Well wait 'til you hear the - you'll kill your sides laughing at this. My goodness. So here - that was all right. I done seven y
ear in there in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. That same chef stays out then in Gluxon, Mr Queeze his name. Quee. So here - I come in the following day and I had to look at the menu - you see to see what was on the lunches. After I'd served breakfast I had to help him with 
the lunches, maybe to cook boiled cabbage, whatever veg he'd got on, had to get the big pot and - the cabbage was all ready for the - night afore in the tub, I had - to strain the water away and - wash it out and then put it in this big - pot when it was 
boiling and put salt in it you see, he didn't need to tell me. And that wasnae my work in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} at all. He had me - he - Beresford, he had me cooking for by, you see, so anyway that was all right so here - he wrote back and he - you see, and - well -
 I had a pair of glasses you know - and it was for the wee hook in them and they flew at me. They flew at me. And this girl Margaret Edgley, she stayed in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, she'd a room in there, 'cos she was away from her husband, and she couldn't get on 
with him - so she stayed in the hotel and she was quite a nice person. Well anyway - she was next in - the head chef Mr Que, the Chinese. So here, he says, what in the name of goodness is up with you? I said - and I'm like this, she's standing - and she's
 
killing her sides laughing and I said, oh my goodness, I would need a - I need a Philadelphia lawyer here, it's transparent that. He said can you not make it out? I said, no I can't. So that was that so you see - well if you've - it's cabbage on the menu.
 
Well I says by gum chef - so that was all right so I went away and I got the cabbage and it took me nearly a week, what he put. I could have lifted and said - I've got the office and - get the girls up there to - to write it so that I could sort of - he s
ayd, he stood there laughing, aye, he says, you'll get there, you're smart enough, he says, away you go, you're - you - you - he says, and so I did - there, took me about a week or a fortnight to follow that menu you know, and he laughed so here -
