\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15823640 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
And then you'd put the food out onto plates ready for the waitresses to serve out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15232123 KS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1067686\charrsid7227600 
Aye. Aye. Aye. Aye, well wait 'til you hear this, this was in George hotel one night
 and - this was me, down the stair in the kitchen this night and Nimmy Giles took the hotplate, it was so stubborn you see. So Margaret - that was - that was next to the chef - head chef, she says, Kathy - go and - eat your supper Kathy, and - if I get bu
s
y I'll shout you out you see. Well - Margaret, you would have killed your sides laughing, you know them big round monocles - you know - aye, you know, well - Mary's father gave me that one night - I didnae go and - and one - I hadna the wee glasses with t
h
e spring on them that you asked me, I'd this big monocle, you know, it was - talk about - mind the time of the vie shilling pieces. Well it was bigger than that, was white. Well - I - I carried it about with me to see the cheques that was coming down for 
-
 to the kitchen if the people didn't go on their dinner they came on down us, and that was maybe - haddock and chips, and pie and chips or - or maybe - fried egg and bacon and chips you know, that was more of the high teas. We working on the food you know
. Well the chef having here in the George - the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}George{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Hotel{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 with the Que, well then I went from that to - what do you call it, Howington canteen, Howington. So that was -
