 the supervisor served with the food there and - what do you call it - the - the manageress was Miss Peterson. She was a Jewess, a lovely woman. So here - I was down at the other end of the canteen with - this Clark, the chef - he was only one chef there,
 
but the women did all the hard work there, potatoes were all put in a - you know the steamers Margaret? You put the boiled potatoes in those steamers you know. Well I'd to do that, but you'd to watch the way you opened the doors otherwise it - you'd have 
