ot roasted you know and - you'd to hold back and open the doors, the handle of the door quick, of the steamer you know and - I don't like - I nearly did get burned one time with it, and the manageress said, no, no, you'd better be careful, so here - the -
 
the - hard work wasn't in it long and - they were going on holiday, it was the fair time you see. So here - no, this was before that, this was - this was before that. I had this great big stove - it was chromium for - all the pots went on for to cook, you
 
see - for - stew or whatever they put on the menu, we'd the Rolls Royce workers in, you know what they are. There's about six hundred there Rolls Royce, the men. Well they come into - oh huge canteen. Well - I didn't serve it up at that time you see. So h
ere - this day we went in on a Saturday usually at eight o'clock, but went in through the week at that time too, and -
