No, nothing. No. She never - she was a very sturdy girl as I said, and how she got - she died with - poisoned kidneys and heart, and it was me that did all the hard work in the house. I did all the washing - and in the steam wash house,
 and you'd to work in they days, no this - rumble thing that they've got now, machines. No, no. And windows and cooking and everything, I don't know how she got it. She was a lovely girl. For she died at twenty-one. Aye.
